                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">re—called</hi>). I executed the order mentioned in the letter of 19th July, 1867—they are the goods I have spoken of—(<hi rend="italic">The letter of 23rd of July</hi>, 1867, <hi rend="italic">was read, at the request of</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SERJEANT PARRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">to show that the order was not executed</hi>)—I did send those goods, and produce the invoice—I have traced those goods—I sent them in the belief that they were to be dealt with in the ordinary way of trade.</p>
